# Aleria V2 — Architecture Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack, SSG)
- React 19, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons
- Deployment: Vercel

## Design System
Full reference: `DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` at repo root.

### Color Palette
- **Light mode first**. Dark mode only via `.dark` class on specific sections.
- Background: Warm Paper — `bg-background`
- Text: Espresso — `text-foreground`
- Contrast sections: Desert Sand Light — `bg-muted`
- Brand accents: Mint — `text-brand-mint` / Sand — `text-brand-sand`

### Text Hierarchy (4 tiers)
- **Primary**: `text-foreground` — headings, strong text
- **Secondary**: `text-muted-foreground` — body text, descriptions
- **Tertiary**: `text-tertiary` — feature details, list descriptions
- **Quaternary**: `text-quaternary` — meta text, footer links, subtle labels
- Do NOT use opacity modifiers on text colors for readable text. Use the semantic tiers.
- Exception: decorative/non-essential elements (e.g. large watermark numbers) may use opacity.

### Brand Gradient Effects
- `.gradient-desert-mint` — solid gradient fill
- `.text-gradient-desert-mint` — gradient text (max 1 per page)
- `.line-gradient` — 1px horizontal separator (header, dividers)
- `.border-gradient` — gradient border on elements
- `.border-gradient-glow` — gradient border + frosted glass + glow (CTA outline)
- `.btn-primary-gradient` — Espresso fill + gradient border (CTA primary)

### Typography
- Headings (h1, h2): **Playfair Display** (serif) — applied globally in CSS
- Body: **Manrope** — `font-sans` (variable: `--font-manrope`)
- Monospace: **Geist Mono** — `font-mono`
- ALWAYS use `.type-*` classes. NEVER combine manual font-size + font-weight + tracking.
- Available: `type-display`, `type-title`, `type-heading`, `type-body`, `type-body-sm`, `type-label`, `type-metric`
- `.type-label` includes auto uppercase + medium weight + wide tracking

### Bold/Light Rule
- Applied on ALL h1 and h2 titles (type-display and type-title)
- The light word (`font-normal`) must be a significant/signature word
- Never a conjunction, article, or last word of the line
- Maximum 1 light word per title

## File rules
- Max 150 lines per file. Split if larger.
- No barrel exports. Import directly.
- No unused imports, variables, or files. Run `npm run lint` before finishing.

## Styling
- All colors from CSS custom properties in `globals.css`.
- Use Tailwind tokens (`text-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `text-tertiary`, `text-quaternary`).
- Never hardcode colors in components.
- Exception: radial gradients for ambient effects may use oklch inline.
- Exception: macOS traffic light dots in `WindowFrame` use standard platform colors.

## Animations
- Import constants from `src/lib/motion.ts`: `EASE`, `DURATION`, `VIEWPORT`, `fadeUp`, `fadeIn`, `stagger`.
- NEVER hardcode ease arrays or duration values inline. Always use the centralized constants.
- Exception: Framer Motion `layoutId` spring transitions may use inline spring config.
- Framer Motion `whileInView` for scroll-triggered.
- Lists use `variants` + `stagger()` function.

## Accessibility
- All decorative elements must have `aria-hidden="true"`.
- Icons inside buttons/links (ArrowRight, ArrowDown, Menu, X, Play, ChevronRight) must have `aria-hidden="true"`.
- Toggle buttons must have `aria-expanded`.
- Navigation landmarks must have `aria-label`.
- All interactive elements must use `.focus-ring` class.
- App is wrapped in `<MotionConfig reducedMotion="user">` via `Providers`.

## Components

### UI primitives (`components/ui/`)
Headless, interaction-focused components. No `"use client"` unless hooks are used.
- `Marquee` — CSS-only infinite scroll. Props: `speed`, `reverse`, `pauseOnHover`. Server component.
- `TextRotator` — Animated word cycling with AnimatePresence. Props: `words`, `interval`. Client component.

### Marketing primitives (`components/marketing/`)
- `Btn` — Polymorphic button/link. Variants: `primary`, `secondary`, `outline_gradient`, `ghost`. Uses `.focus-ring`.
- `Section` — Section wrapper. Props: `background` (`default`/`muted`/`dark`), `spacing` (`default`/`lg`/`none`), `divider`.
- `Container` — Max-width wrapper. Props: `size` (`default`/`narrow`/`wide`/`full`). Responsive padding: `px-5 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`.
- `Badge` — Section label. Auto `type-label` styling.
- `LinkArrow` — Text link with animated arrow. Uses `.focus-ring`.
- `WindowFrame` — macOS-style window chrome (traffic light dots + optional title). Props: `title`, `children`. Server component.
- `SectionHeader` — Badge + title + description with `fadeUp` animation. Props: `badge`, `title` (ReactNode), `description`, `align`, `size` (`default`/`lg`).
- `HoneycombBg` — Decorative SVG hex grid background. Props: `placement` (8 positions), `intensity` (`subtle`/`medium`/`strong`). Max 5 per page, unique placements, max 1 `strong`.

### Sections (`components/sections/home/`)
- One file per section, named by content. Sub-components split into `{section}-{part}.tsx`.
- Each section receives `{ className?: string }` via `SectionProps`.

#### Homepage section order and patterns:
1. **Hero** (`hero.tsx` + `hero-clients.tsx`) — Full viewport, announcement pill, h1, CTAs, logo marquee. Default bg. HoneycombBg: `top-left` subtle + `bottom-right` strong.
2. **Ecosystem** (`ecosystem.tsx` + `ecosystem-tabs.tsx`) — SectionHeader, segmented process block (Build→Deploy→Operate with arrows), tabbed product showcase (WindowFrame). Default bg.
3. **Why Teams** (`why-teams.tsx` + `why-teams-grid.tsx` + `deployed-banner.tsx`) — TextRotator headline, bento grid (sand bg cells + espresso accent cells), CTA, deployed banner (espresso block with case studies). Default bg. HoneycombBg: `top-right` subtle.
4. **AI Factory** (`ai-factory.tsx`) — Asymmetric layout: text+icons left, WindowFrame right. Default bg.
5. **Sources** (`sources.tsx`) — Asymmetric reversed: WindowFrame left, text+stats right. Muted bg + dividers. HoneycombBg: `top-center` subtle.
6. **AI OS** (`ai-os.tsx`) — Centered header, tabs (AI Employees / Flows), WindowFrame + features side by side. Default bg.
7. **More Products** (`more-products.tsx`) — 2-column WindowFrame cards (Dashboard AI, Video AI). Dark bg + dividers.
8. **Closing CTA** (`closing-cta.tsx`) — Emotional h2, gradient divider, 2 CTAs. Container narrow. Default bg. HoneycombBg: `bottom-center` medium.

#### Section background rhythm:
`default → default → default → default → muted → default → dark → default`
Muted and dark sections always have `divider="both"`.

#### Layout patterns used:
- **Centered**: SectionHeader → content → CTA (Ecosystem, More Products)
- **Asymmetric**: text left + visual right, or reversed (AI Factory, Sources)
- **Tabbed**: tabs bar + animated content swap (Ecosystem tabs, AI OS)
- **Bento grid**: mixed col-span/row-span with accent cells (Why Teams)
- **Embedded banner**: dark block within a section (Deployed banner in Why Teams)

#### Section spacing system:
- Section padding default: `py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28`
- Section padding large: `py-20 sm:py-24 lg:py-32`
- SectionHeader → content: `mt-14`
- Content → CTA: `mt-10`
- Asymmetric grid gap: `gap-10 lg:gap-16`

### Layout (`components/layout/`)
- `header.tsx` — transparent blur + `.line-gradient` separator. Height: `var(--header-height)`.
- `footer.tsx`, `mobile-nav.tsx`
- Logo: `/public/logo.svg` (light) and `/public/logo-dark.svg` (dark sections)

## Removed components (do NOT recreate)
- `MediaFrame` — replaced by `WindowFrame` for product screenshots
- `ProductCard` — replaced by direct WindowFrame + text layouts
- `CaseStudyCard` — replaced by deployed banner inline layout
- `Metric` / `MetricRow` — replaced by inline stat blocks

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT combine manual font-size + font-weight + tracking. Use `.type-*` classes.
- Do NOT use gradient as section background fill.
- Do NOT use `.text-gradient-desert-mint` on more than 1 element per page.
- Do NOT add icon-in-a-box patterns. Use typography and whitespace.
- Do NOT add `"use client"` unless the component uses hooks or event handlers.
- Do NOT create hooks or utilities unless used by 2+ files.
- Do NOT hardcode ease/duration values. Import from `@/lib/motion`.
- Do NOT use opacity modifiers for text hierarchy. Use `text-tertiary` / `text-quaternary`.
- Do NOT use more than 5 HoneycombBg per page, and never the same placement twice. Use at most one `strong` per page.
- Do NOT recreate removed components (MediaFrame, ProductCard, CaseStudyCard, Metric).

